==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Philomela
<hw>Phil`o*me"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>philomela</ets>, Gr. <grk>filomh`la</grk>, according to the legend,
from <grk>Filomh`la</grk> <persfn>Philomela</persfn> (daughter of
<persfn>Pandion</persfn>, king of Athens), who was changed into a
nightingale.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The nightingale; philomel.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of birds including the
nightingales.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Philomene</ent>⟦br⟧
